text: Lainey Denay Wilson (born on May 19, 1992 in Baskin, Louisiana) is an American country musician, singer-songwriter and recording artist. She released her first studio album under the Cupit record label. The album was self-titled. Her other studio albums include The Bell Bottom Country. Wilson received a Grammy Award, seven CMA Awards and six Academy of Country Music Awards. She was later raised in Nashville, Tennessee and graduated high school in 2010 or 2011. ==References== Category:American country musicians Category:American country singers Category:Singers from Nashville, Tennessee Category:Singers from Louisiana Category:American Grammy Award winners Category:Living people Category:1992 births
